Subject: Re: [T2] Wipers SLOW when cold

Michael Benthin (MUTS) sends:

> When cold (like 32 outside, these mornings), my wipers (78 Westy) go
> rather slowly; is this due to the motor gear grease getting old or
> something stiff in the pantograph stuff rotating the arms?  Being
> reluctant to pull anything with all that stuff in the way, what works
> best as a spray solution- WD40 (dries up?), Liquid Wrench (ditto), spray
> grease (too thick to penetrate?)....any experence on this??

I'd cover the Bus floor under the dash with newspapers, squirt the
pantograph joints with WD-40 until the drippings run clear (this to clean
the system out), give it a day to dry, then put silicone spray on them.
